  OF COLING-92, NANTES, AUG. 23-28, 1992 3) How LEXTER works : analysis and parsing To detect erminological units, LEXTER takes the form of these units into consideration, and works in two phases : analysis and parsing.
  LEXTER treats categorized texts, which have been submitted to a morphological nalysis : each word is tagged with its grammatical category (noun, verb, adjective, etc.).
